Global USB-To-Serial Adapter Market Insights
USB-To-Serial Adapter Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

USB-To-Serial Adapter Market Overview
The USB-to-Serial Adapter market has experienced significant growth, with the global market size valued at approximately USD 1.2 billion in 2022. Projections indicate an increase to USD 2.0 billion by 2030, reflecting a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.3% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is driven by the increasing adoption of industrial automation, the proliferation of the Internet of Things (IoT), and the rising demand for connectivity solutions across various industries. The market is segmented by type into USB-to-RS232, USB-to-RS485, and USB-to-TTL adapters, with USB-to-RS232 adapters holding the largest market share due to their widespread use in connecting computers to serial devices such as printers, scanners, and modems. Regionally, North America and Europe dominate the market, followed by Asia Pacific, attributed to the high adoption of industrial automation and the presence of major technology hubs in these regions.

